@Node "1" "AMaster.guide/1"
@Next "2"
@Prev "Main"

  What is AMaster:


  AMaster is simply said, just a little address data base.

  It has a lot of features and functions, that are not normal standard
  for FD programs.

  The main reason for using AMaster (refered now with AM) is not to
  to replace commercial products such as SuperBase or DBase etc., but
  its a small, easy to handle, and cheap (free) data base.

  I wrote this program because I needed it and some other data bases
  which are written often badly and that are released as shareware,
  are not worth for me to sending them any money.


  Okay but now come to the more interested stuff...

@Endnode

@Node "2" "AMaster.guide/2"
@Next "3"
@Prev "1"

  Features:

  AM has a lot of features, so I will describe only the most important
  ones:

      -   Am is font independent, that means: AM sizes its windows and
          gadgets dependent to the currently used workbench font. This
          is the Standartfont which can be set by the `SYS:Prefs/Font`
          program.

      -   As many entries for each File as you want (only dependent
          to your free memory),

      -   Filerequester-support for all save and load operations,

      -   You can save all settings in a preferences file,

      -   Sorting with each field in normal and updside down direction
          (from a to z or from z to a). The maximal number of entries
          for sorting procedures are 10000 (!) entries.

      -   Selections supports standart patter matching (#?,##,[],~#? ...)

      -   Selections with each field with an alternatively case sensitivity.

      -   Iconify function,

      -   Moving through the entries with Slider Gadgets and cursor keys or
          with a goto requester,

      -   Full Intuition- (GadTools-) user-interface,

      -   Full mouse- and keyboard driven,

      -   Online help system for each Gadget, keyboard command, shortcut and
          menu,

      -   Dynamically memory allocations,

      -   A lot of printer options, left , right, top offset, pagelength
          and the ability to exclude or include each field of the base
          for the print out,

      -   Printing to the printer, in a file or even to the screen,

      -   Progress indicator for running operations.

      -   Fully written under OS 2.xx,

      -   well outfit (ahemm)...

@Endnode

@Node "3" "AMaster.guide/3"
@Next "4"
@Prev "2"

 System Requirements:

    AMaster uses a lot of kickstart 2.04 routins and is therefor
    not able to run under previous versions.

    AM should run on all amigas with 512k memory and uses the currently
    activated printer driver.

@Endnode

