 CLI-Parameters:

    Syntax:     AMaster File,Prefs=P/K,Icon=I/S,Help=H/S:

    with


        File    :   This is the name of a file which was saved from
                    AM. Default: none.

        Prefs   :   This is a configuration file, which should be used
                    Default: ENV:AMaster.prefs
                             ENVARC:AMaster.prefs
                    If none of these both files can be loaded AM uses
                    its internal settings.

        Icon    :   If you specify Icon, AM starts in iconified mode.
                    That means only a small window will appear instead
                    of the normal main window. Clicking on the ZipGadget
                    (left from the depth gadget) brings the window to its
                    normal size.
                    Default: OFF

        Help    :   Instead of starting AM it just prints out a little
                    help message. This message also appears if you give
                    AM a wrong commandline.


@Endnode

@Node "6" "AMaster.guide/6"
@Next "7"
@Prev "5"

 WBench ToolTypes:

    Supported by AMaster:

        FILE    =   <Name of the Project to load>

        PREFS   =   <Name of the configuration file>

        ICONIFY =   <TRUE|FALSE>

    Supported by System:

        ToolPri =   <Priority of the program>

        CLI     :   A requester openes and lets you specify commandline
                    arguments for AM.


    To start AM with a data file you can also multiselect the data files`s
    Icon and the AM`s icon and doubleclick.

@Endnode

@Node "7" "AMaster.guide/7"
@Next "8"
@Prev "6"

 Intuition Interface:

    AMaster has a fully mousedriven intuition interface. That means
    all functions can be started by clicking gadgets or using the
    keyboard or selecting a menuitem.

    For almost every gadget exists a key which can be pressed instead
    of using the mouse. This key is usually displayed underlined.
    For some keys exists no normal printable character, e.g. the cursor
    keys, escape,return etc. Some gadgets can be aktivated by using one
    of these special characters.

    For some operations which will take a little time, a small window
    will be opened which will displays a progress indicator and a little
    information text. The text tells you what AM is currently doing and
    the indicator displays the progress in percent. 100 % means the
    function is finished.
    Dependent on your computer type and system, there can be different
    speeds for this functions.

    On those functions that takes a little more time the window will be
    disabled. That means that the mousepointer will change into a ZZ-
    pointer. When the old pointer comes back the function is finished
    and the window is then be active and enabled and ready to start new
    actions.
    While a window is disabled all mouseclicks or keyboard actions will be
    ignored.

    This program is written fully under OS 2.04 and for this reason there
    exists all well known different kinds of gadget types. They should be
    discribed here very short. For further explanations please refer to
    your amigados manual.

@Endnode

@Node "8" "AMaster.guide/8"
@Next "9"
@Prev "7"

 OS 2.04 Gadgets:

    BUTTON_GADGET:

        This button will be displayed recessed when you click on its
        image with the left mousebutton. If you release the button on
        its imagenary the function will be started.

    CHECKBOX_GADGET:

        This gadget have two states. If this gadget is activated the hook
        is visual otherwise not.

    STRING_GADGET:

        This gadget enables you to easily edit a short text which is
        displayed in the gadget box. After pressing the return key, the
        editing is finished.

        If you press the underlined key the gadget becomes activated and
        you can suddenly start to edit the text.

    CYCLE_GADGET:

        This kind of gadget displays one selection from a list.
        By clicking on this gadget the next selection is displayed.

        If you use the underlined key its exactly the same than clicking
        on this gadget. If you press the underlined key together with the
        SHIFT key, the previous selection will be displayed.

    MX_Gadget:

        Here you can select also a selection. But you can see all kinds
        of selections at the same time. If you activate one entry the
        previously selected one will be automatically deselected.

    SLIDER_GADGET:

        The body of the gadget (mostly in black) displays the relation
        between the total amount of elements to the currently number of
        displayed elements. If you klick under or above the body but in
        the gadgetbox you scrolls to the next (previous) page. If you
        click on the body and hold down the mousebutton you can get a
        continously moving.

        Also here does the underlined key together with the SHIFT key a
        scroll back.

@Endnode

@Node "9" "AMaster.guide/9"
@Next "10"
@Prev "8"

 AMaster Help System:

    Because of AM`s help system AM is also interested for new
    amiga maniacs :-). Pressing the help key on one of AM`s
    windows, will change to help mode. Pressing a key or clicking
    on a gadget or selecting a menu will then open a helpwindow
    which will discribe the function for this action.

    To change to normal mode you just have to press the help
    key a second time.

@Endnode

@Node "10" "AMaster.guide/10"
@Next "11"
@Prev "9"

 The Main Window:

    This is the window which will be first opened when you start
    AMaster.

    The title will show you the name of the current project. After
    this name there follwos three characters which represents the
    states of some configuration modes.

    If the character is in lower case its not active, else its
    activated.

    (m) or (M)

    displays whether the project has been modified or not.

    (s) oder (S)

    displays whether the project is currently selected or not
    (see later).

    (e) oder (E)

    displays whether the editmode is selcted or not.


    The main window has two main sections.

    On the left hand side there are all the gadgets for displaying the
    entries, moving inside the project remove and add several entries.
    On the right hand side there are gadgets for selecting, sorting and
    printing.


    The gadgets on the left side:


    Family Name Gadget (Key `a`)

    This gadget displays the contents of the family name field of the
    current entry.
    If you are in editmode you can freely edit the contents. Otherwise
    you can just activate  tehe gadget and change the text but the contents
    will not be saved into the base (in memory).
    This behaviour is much the same with all string gadgets on this side
    of the window.

    This gadget is available in editmode also with pressing the return key.

    Name Gadget (Key `m`)

    Displays the contents of the name field.

    Street Gadget (Key `r`)

    Displays the contents of the street field.

    Stadt Gadget (`c`)

    Displays the contents of the city field.

    State Gadget (`t`)

    Displays the contents of the state field.

    Phone Gadget (`o`)

    Displays the contents of the phone number field.

    Note Gadget (`n`)

    Displays the contents of the note field of the current entry.
    If you leave this gadget with return, and if you are in edit
    mode, the next entry will be displayed. If you are just on the
    last entry, a new empty entry will be added.
    If not in editmode the first entry will be displayed.

    All these gadgets are read-only gadgets if not in edit mode.
    Otherwise each editing will be suddenly saved to the data
    base (in memory).

    The keyboard commands in a stringgadget are:

    right amiga key + x

        deletes the whole text in the gadget

    right amiga key + q

        undos a deletion with a-x

    Backspace

        deletes the charcter before the cursor

    Delete

        deletes the charcter under the cursor.

    TAB

        activates the next string available gadget

    Shift TAB

        activates the previous string gadget


    Record: Gadget

        This is a information (TEXT) gadget. Its displays the current
        entry and the total number of entries in the current base.

    Slider Gadget

    The slider gadget can be used to move through the base.

    New Entry (`w`) Gadget

    This gadget inserts a new entry before the currently displayed
    one.

    This functions is also only available in edit mode.

    Remove (`v`) Gadget

    This gadget deletes the current record.
    Like all other functions which will modify the project, this
    function is only available in edit mode.

    |< Gadget (Cursor Up)

    Jumps to the first entry in the current project

    << Gadget (Pfeiltaste links)

    Displays the previous entry.

    Goto Gadget (`g`)

    Openes a little window which lets you insert the number of
    an entry you wants to jump to.
    The available range will be displayed in the window text.
    Other values outside this range will be ignored.
    With cancel you can close the window without any moving.

    >> Gadget (Cursor Right)

    Displays the next entry.
    If in edit mode  and you have reached the last entry a new
    empty entry will be added.

    >| Gadget (Pfeiltaste unten)

    Jumps to the last entry of the project.



    The gadgets on the right side of the main window:


    Search Gadget (`S`)

    This starts the search or selection process. The whole data
    base will be compared, entry for entry, for a match with the
    string in the Text string gadget. The field for this matching
    process will be given by the selection of the field 0 gadget.
    Each matching entry will be copied in a new list. After this
    function has been finished the new list will be displayed.
    The project has been selected.

    Th see whether you see the selected list or the normal you can
    look at the (s) or (S) in the window title. If the s is in upper
    case you will see the selected list.

    To change to normal mode you have to press the search gadget again.
    If AM doesn`t find any matching entry, no selection list will be
    displayed. Also if the pattern in the Text string gadget has been
    to vague, that each entry matches the pattern, the selection list
    will be automatically reselected.


    Case Sensitivity (`.`)

    If this checkbox is active the matching procedure makes a difference
    between lower and upper case.

    Field 0 Gadget (`0` or `=`)

    This is the search field selection.
    The selection procedure searches for a match dependent on the search
    field. E.G. if the search field is set to name and the serachtext is
    set to `Har` so Harold, Hardy etc... will be matched.

    Text StringGadget (`x`)

    This is the searchtext. Its a pattern which may contain all amigados
    standart patterns such as #?, ##, ~(a|h).#? etc.

    Sort Gadget (`s`)

    This gadget start the sort process. If the base is currently selected
    it will be reselected automatically. The field after which should be
    sorted, is indicated by the field 1 gadget.

    The maximum allowed number of entries for the sort procedure is currently
    by 10000. If you have more entries in your base, only the first 10000 will
    be sorted.

    The speed of this process is right dependent to the size of your data base.
    For smaller bases (<= 1000) this process is very fast. If your base is
    bigger, you can make you a coffee(:-)).

    Field 1 Gadget (`1` or `!`)

    This is the sort field selection. The data base will be sorted
    dependent to this field.

    from z - a Gadget (`-`)

    If this checkbox is active, the project will be sorted in the other
    direction, instead from a to z , now from z to a.



    The next section contains the most importent functions of AM.

    Print Window Gadget (`i`)

    This gadget opens the Print Window, which will be descriped later
    in this manual.

    Prefs Window (`f`)

    This gadget opens the Preferences Window which will be also
    described later.

    About Gadget (`A`) or menuitem: Project/About

    This opens a requester which will display some informations about
    the program and the author. Also the total bytes of free memory,
    the number of entries in the base and the current project name
    will be displayed.

    Open Gadget (`b`) or menuitem: Project/Open Project

    If no project has been loaded, a filerequester will be opened
    which lets you select a new project, otherwise the current
    project will be loaded again. You should use for all projects
    the suffix `.dat`. Because AM is able to recognize all files
    with this suffix automatically.

    (TAKE CARE: Do never load a file which was not saved within
                AM. This file may use a wrong format is you get
                the risk of a system-crash.)

    Save Gadget (`p`) or menuitem: Project/Save

    If the current project is `unnamed` a filerequester will be opened
    that lets you select a new name for the project. Otherwise the
    project will be saved under the current name.
    Also in this case you should always use the suffix `.dat` for the
    name.

    Edit Gadget (`e`)

    Toggles between read-only and edit mode.

    Help Gadget (`h` or Help key) or menuitem: Project/Help

    Changes to help mode. A second activation of this gadget changes
    back to normal mode.

    Quit Gadget (`q` or ESCAPE key) or menuitem: Project/Quit

    Quits AM. If the current project and the current settings have
    been modified, a requester will be opned with the maximal 5
    gadgets:

    SaveProject :   Only the project should be saved (by using the
                    filerequester)
    SavePrefs   :   Only the prefernces file should be saved
                    (filerequester)
    Save All    :   The project and the settings should be saved

    Quit        :   Quit without any savings

    Cancel      :   Cancel the action and return to AMaster


    There are also some other menuitems without aquivalent gadgets:


    Project Menu:

    Select Project

    Opens the filerequester and lets you select a new file to load.

    Save As ...

    Opens the filerequester and lets you chose a new name for the
    project.


    Preferences Menu:

    In this menu there are some functions, which are also on the prefs
    window. Here you can save. load and reload the settings, without
    the need to change to the prefs window.

    Open Preferences

    Opens the default preferences file(s) which is
    `ENV:AMaster.prefs`. If this file cannot be loaded AM tries to open
    `ENVARC:AMaster.prefs`.

    Select Preferences

    Opens the filerequester which let you select a configuration file.

    Save Preferences

    Save the current setting in the default preferences files.

    Save Preferences As ...

    Opens the filerequester which let you select a new name for the
    setting file.

    With Icons

    If this menuitem is activated, all projects and prefs files will
    be saved with icons.

@Endnode

@Node "11" "AMaster.guide/11"
@Next "12"
@Prev "10"

 The Preferences Window:

    If you click on the Prefs Window gadget on the main window the
    Preferences Window will be opened. It has a lot of gadgets. Some
    of theses gadgets are also available on other windows.
    All options, texts, paths etc. can be changed and saved here. New
    settings files can be loaded.
    If you haven`t specify a prefs file at start time, AM loads the
    default settings file.

    The first section of this window handles the printer parameters.

    The Gadgets:

    All CheckBox (`y`)

    If this checkbox is activated, all fields of the entries will be
    selected for a print out. All other checkboxes in this section will
    be inactivated.
    If you select one of the other checkboxes in this section, the All
    checkbox will be automatically deactivated.

    Numbers CheckBox (`u`)

    If this checkbox is activated for each entry a number will be printed
    out (starting at 1).

    Family Name CheckBox (`a`)

    If this checkbox is activated the family name fields will be printed
    out.

    Name CheckBox (`m`)

    If this checkbox is activated the name fields will be printed out.

    Street CheckBox (`r`)

    If this checkbox is activated the street fields will be printed out.

    City CheckBox (`c`)

    If this checkbox is activated the city fields will be printed out.
                             AMaster.doc  Page 11

    State CheckBox (`t`)

    If this checkbox is activated the state fields will be printed out.

    Phone CheckBox (`o`)

    If this checkbox is activated the phone number fields will be printed
    out.

    Note CheckBox (`n`)

    If this checkbox is activated the note fields will be printed out.


    Right beneth the checkboxes there are three sliders which specifies
    the pagelength, left and right offset for the print out.

    Left Offset Slider (`l` or `L`)

    This is the number of chars which should be used as the left offset
    for the print out. Maximum is 99 and minimum is chars

    Top Offset Slider (`p` or `P`)

    This is the number of empty lines which should be used as the top
    offset for the print out. Maximum is 99 and minimum is 0 lines.

    Pagelength Slider (`g` or `G`)

    This is the number of lines per page which should be used for a
    print out. After each page a requester will be opned which will
    ask you to go on or to cancel the print out.

    If you e.g. set the pagelength to 10 and the top offset to 1 you
    will get exactly one entry per page.
    Maximum is 150 minimum is 10 lines per page.

    File StringGadget (`f`)

    The contents of this string gadget will be used for the print out.
    Normally this would be `prt:`. But you can also specify here another
    name or file. With `prt:` the preferences printer driver will be used.
    If you use PAR: no text formatting informations will be send to the
    printer.
    If you specify a file name  instead, the print out goes to disk.

    !!! Warning !!! A printout to disk cannot (never) be loaded as
                    a project, because the left, top offset and the num-
                    berings could not be understanded by AM.
                    Therefor donot use the suffix `.dat` for any print
                    out.

    Select File Gadget (`2`)

    Openes the filerequester to chose a name for the print out.

    Now follows the section for the search parameters.

    Field 0 Gadget (`0` or `=`)

    This is the field to search for.

    Case Sensitivity (`i`)

    If this checkbox is active the comparing of the pattern matching
    is done case dependent.

    Pattern StringGadget (`P`)

    This is the searchtext to compare the entries with.

    Now follows the section for the sort parameters.

    Field 1 Gadget (`1` or `!`)

    Specifies the field to sort with.

    Sort Direction Gadget (`.`)

    If this checkbox is activated the sortdirection will be toggled.
    Not activated, the sort direction start from a and ends with z.

    Path for help files Gadget or (`h`)

    For the help system AM uses several help files. The contents of this
    string gadget specifies the location of this help files. Default
    path is here `ENV:AMHelp`. If you want to copy the helpfiles to another
    location you may simply change this path.

    Path Selection Gadget (`3`)

    Opens a filerequetsre which let you select the new path for the help
    files.


    Under this section there are two gadgets which handle higher priority
    settings, that means they specify how AM starts.

    Starting in editing mode Gadget (`e`)

    AM starts in edit mode. Take care not to overwrite projects.

    Startinf Iconified (`I`)

    AM starts in iconified mode. This does the same than the Icon
    commandline argument.

    Now there are some action gadgets.

    Open Gadget (`O`)

    Loads the default configuration file.

    Select Gadget (`S`)

    Opens the filerequester to select the new prefs file.

    Save Gadget (`s`)

    Saves the current settings to the default files.

    Save As ... (`v`)

    Opens the filerequester which lets you chose another name for the
    prefs file. Please use here the suffix `.prefs`.

    Use Gadget (`U`)

    Uses all modifications closes the prefs window and returns to the main
    window.

    Cancel Gadget (`C` or ESCAPE)

    Uses the old settings before the prefs window has been opned.
    The window will be closed.

@Endnode

@Node "12" "AMaster.guide/12"
@Next "13"
@Prev "11"

 The Print Window:

    If you click on the Print gadget of the main window the Print Window
    will be opned.

    On this window you can set the printer parameters too and perform
    a print out.

    The first section is aquivalent to the print parameters section on
    the Prefs window so I will not describe it here again.

    The Output section is the same as on the Prefs window which contains
    the name of the print out (usually prt:).

    The only new gadget in this section is the mx gadget.

    Screen/Printer Gadget (`+` or `-`)

    This mx gadget specifies whether to perform a print out to the
    file which is represented by the Output gadget or to screen.

    If you chose screen, the Display-Window will be opned, which is
    the same window as the help window. It displays exactly the same
    text as the print out to disk ot prt:.

    The moving of the text and the controlling of the help window will
    be described later.

    The slider gadgets left and right offset and pagelength have also
    the same meaning than the ones on the prefs window.

    Print Gadget (`i`)

    Starts the print out. If you have chosen a print out to printer or
    file, a requester will be opened which lets you proceed or cancel.
    This requester will appears after each printed page.

    Cancel Gadget (`C`)

    Leaves the Print Window.

    All settings which will be modified on this window (except the
    screen/file selection) will be saved to the current settings.

@Endnode

@Node "13" "AMaster.guide/13"
@Next "14"
@Prev "12"

 The Help Window:

    Like said before AM has its own help system. If you press the help
    key on one of the windows, the help mode is activated.
    If you click now on a gadget or press a key, the help window will
    be opened and display the actions which would normally performed by
    this gadget.

    The help window is just a simple textviewer. It doesn`t contain a
    soft scrolling or search function, because of the program size.

    The helpwindow itself has also a help funktion, which lets a requester
    open which displays all gadget and keyboard commands :-).

    The size of the help window depends on your WBench screen size.
    Because of this you will get the maximum lines displayed.

    Now we are coming to the movement:

    |< Gadget or (`t` or CONTROL + Cursor Up)

    Jumps to the start of the text.

    << Gadget or (`P` or Cursor Left or SHIFT + Cursor Up)

    Jumps one page back.

    < Gadget or (`p` or Cursor Up)

    Scrolls one line back.

    > Gadget or (`n` or Cursor Down)

    Scrolls one line down.

    >> Gadget or (`N` or Cursor Right or SHIFT + Cursor Down)

    Jumps one page down.

    >| Gadget or (`b` or CONTROL + Cursor Down)

    Jumps to the end of the text.

    Quit Gadget  or (`q` or ESCAPE)

    Closes the help window.

@Endnode

@Node "14" "AMaster.guide/14"
@Next "15"
@Prev "13"

